mingmin, a minimal version of GMIN written in python.  GMIN was originally
written by David Wales and is desiged to find the global energy minimum for
molecular systems

http://www-wales.ch.cam.ac.uk/software.html


Compilation is required for use of the fast potentials, those written in C++ and/or fortran)

To use the fortran potentials you need f2py, which is part of the numpy package

To use the C++ potentials you need to have boost-python, boost-dev and python-dev installed

to compile:

$ cmake .
$ make 


PYTHONPATH:  
make sure to add the directory mingmin/ to your PYTHONPATH environment variable


=== running ===
see the examples in the examples folder
